{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BiN6nYfXV8pKUmE1UsL61E","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→* Block 08: Mode Control\n     2→* PVDD 5V LDO Regulator — SkyWater SKY130A\n     3→*\n     4→* Subcircuit ports:\n     5→*   bvdd      — battery supply input (0–10.5V), the signal being monitored\n     6→*   pvdd      — regulated supply (5.0V, when available)\n     7→*   svdd      — low-voltage digital supply (2.2V)\n     8→*   gnd       — ground\n     9→*   vref      — bandgap reference 1.226V\n    10→*   en_ret    — retention enable input (SVDD domain, 0/2.2V)\n    11→*   bypass_en — output: enable bypass switch (BVDD domain)\n    12→*   ea_en     — output: enable error amplifier (PVDD domain)\n    13→*   ref_sel   — output: reference select (0=5.0V target, 1=4.1V target)\n    14→*   uvov_en   — output: enable UV/OV comparators\n    15→*   ilim_en   — output: enable current limiter\n    16→*   pass_off  — output: BVDD-domain hard shutoff (drives HV NMOS gate pull-up to BVDD during POR)\n    17→*              NOTE: error amp (Block 00) runs from PVDD=5V and cannot pull pass gate above 5V.\n    18→*              At BVDD=10.5V, pass device gate needs >=9.7V for full shutoff — unreachable from 5V.\n    19→*              pass_off must drive a sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 pulling gate to BVDD.\n    20→*              pass_off is HIGH (active) during POR (BVDD < 2.5V entry threshold).\n    21→*\n    22→* STATUS: EMPTY — threshold detection topology not yet chosen\n    23→*\n    24→* Operating modes (5 total):\n    25→*   Mode 1: POR           BVDD 0–2.5V    PVDD=OFF\n    26→*   Mode 2: Ret bypass    BVDD 2.5–4.2V  PVDD=BVDD (bypass)\n    27→*   Mode 3: Ret regulate  BVDD 4.2–4.5V  PVDD=4.1V (regulated, low power)\n    28→*   Mode 4: PU bypass     BVDD 4.5–5.0V  PVDD=BVDD (bypass)\n    29→*   Mode 5: Active        BVDD > 5.6V    PVDD=5.0V (full regulation)\n    30→*\n    31→* Four threshold comparators needed:\n    32→*   TH1 (POR):       BVDD = 2.5V ± 0.2V, hysteresis 200 mV\n    33→*   TH2 (Ret):       BVDD = 4.2V ± 0.2V, hysteresis 200 mV\n    34→*   TH3 (PU bypass): BVDD = 4.5V ± 0.2V, hysteresis 200 mV\n    35→*   TH4 (Active):    BVDD = 5.6V ± 0.2V, hysteresis 200 mV\n    36→*\n    37→* Recommended topology:\n    38→*   Single resistor ladder from BVDD to GND with 4 tap points.\n    39→*   Four comparators (sky130 HV diff pair) each compare a tap to vref.\n    40→*   Ensures monotonic threshold ordering by design (shared ladder).\n    41→*   SR latches for hysteresis on each comparator output.\n    42→*\n    43→* Requirements:\n    44→*   All 4 thresholds within ±15% of nominal across all PVT\n    45→*   Each hysteresis 150–250 mV\n    46→*   Glitch-free transitions (no intermediate states on outputs)\n    47→*   Works at BVDD ramp rates 0.1–12 V/µs\n    48→*   Quiescent current in active mode <= 20 µA from BVDD\n    49→*   Known issue #m3: glitchy mode outputs cause PVDD oscillation — design clean.\n    50→*\n    51→.subckt mode_control bvdd pvdd svdd gnd vref en_ret bypass_en ea_en ref_sel uvov_en ilim_en pass_off\n    52→\n    53→* TODO: implement mode control here\n    54→* Build incrementally: one comparator at a time.\n    55→* Start with TH4 (active mode threshold) since it is used in standalone testing.\n    56→*\n    57→* Step 1: single resistor ladder (BVDD → R_top → tap4 → ... → tap1 → R_bot → GND)\n    58→* Step 2: comparator for TH4 — tap4 vs vref\n    59→* Step 3: add hysteresis (SR latch or positive feedback)\n    60→* Step 4: logic to generate ea_en, bypass_en, etc.\n    61→* Step 5: add remaining 3 comparators\n    62→\n    63→.ends mode_control\n    64→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"314d5c08-cf8c-4a8a-998c-ea971d7c74fa","timestamp":"2026-03-29T14:59:43.791Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/pvdd_regulator/08_mode_control/design.cir","content":"* Block 08: Mode Control\n* PVDD 5V LDO Regulator — SkyWater SKY130A\n*\n* Subcircuit ports:\n*   bvdd      — battery supply input (0–10.5V), the signal being monitored\n*   pvdd      — regulated supply (5.0V, when available)\n*   svdd      — low-voltage digital supply (2.2V)\n*   gnd       — ground\n*   vref      — bandgap reference 1.226V\n*   en_ret    — retention enable input (SVDD domain, 0/2.2V)\n*   bypass_en — output: enable bypass switch (BVDD domain)\n*   ea_en     — output: enable error amplifier (PVDD domain)\n*   ref_sel   — output: reference select (0=5.0V target, 1=4.1V target)\n*   uvov_en   — output: enable UV/OV comparators\n*   ilim_en   — output: enable current limiter\n*   pass_off  — output: BVDD-domain hard shutoff (drives HV NMOS gate pull-up to BVDD during POR)\n*              NOTE: error amp (Block 00) runs from PVDD=5V and cannot pull pass gate above 5V.\n*              At BVDD=10.5V, pass device gate needs >=9.7V for full shutoff — unreachable from 5V.\n*              pass_off must drive a sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 pulling gate to BVDD.\n*              pass_off is HIGH (active) during POR (BVDD < 2.5V entry threshold).\n*\n* STATUS: EMPTY — threshold detection topology not yet chosen\n*\n* Operating modes (5 total):\n*   Mode 1: POR           BVDD 0–2.5V    PVDD=OFF\n*   Mode 2: Ret bypass    BVDD 2.5–4.2V  PVDD=BVDD (bypass)\n*   Mode 3: Ret regulate  BVDD 4.2–4.5V  PVDD=4.1V (regulated, low power)\n*   Mode 4: PU bypass     BVDD 4.5–5.0V  PVDD=BVDD (bypass)\n*   Mode 5: Active        BVDD > 5.6V    PVDD=5.0V (full regulation)\n*\n* Four threshold comparators needed:\n*   TH1 (POR):       BVDD = 2.5V ± 0.2V, hysteresis 200 mV\n*   TH2 (Ret):       BVDD = 4.2V ± 0.2V, hysteresis 200 mV\n*   TH3 (PU bypass): BVDD = 4.5V ± 0.2V, hysteresis 200 mV\n*   TH4 (Active):    BVDD = 5.6V ± 0.2V, hysteresis 200 mV\n*\n* Recommended topology:\n*   Single resistor ladder from BVDD to GND with 4 tap points.\n*   Four comparators (sky130 HV diff pair) each compare a tap to vref.\n*   Ensures monotonic threshold ordering by design (shared ladder).\n*   SR latches for hysteresis on each comparator output.\n*\n* Requirements:\n*   All 4 thresholds within ±15% of nominal across all PVT\n*   Each hysteresis 150–250 mV\n*   Glitch-free transitions (no intermediate states on outputs)\n*   Works at BVDD ramp rates 0.1–12 V/µs\n*   Quiescent current in active mode <= 20 µA from BVDD\n*   Known issue #m3: glitchy mode outputs cause PVDD oscillation — design clean.\n*\n.subckt mode_control bvdd pvdd svdd gnd vref en_ret bypass_en ea_en ref_sel uvov_en ilim_en pass_off\n\n* TODO: implement mode control here\n* Build incrementally: one comparator at a time.\n* Start with TH4 (active mode threshold) since it is used in standalone testing.\n*\n* Step 1: single resistor ladder (BVDD → R_top → tap4 → ... → tap1 → R_bot → GND)\n* Step 2: comparator for TH4 — tap4 vs vref\n* Step 3: add hysteresis (SR latch or positive feedback)\n* Step 4: logic to generate ea_en, bypass_en, etc.\n* Step 5: add remaining 3 comparators\n\n.ends mode_control\n","numLines":64,"startLine":1,"totalLines":64}}}
