{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Wzv38V5FCqKkKyHZuuZghh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! Now the values are L=1e-4 and W=2e-5, which are exactly Lmax=1e-4 and Wmin=2e-5 from the model. But it still fails! This means the boundary check is exclusive (L < Lmax, not L <= Lmax).\n\nLet me try L=99e-6 instead of L=100e-6.\n\nWait, actually, I recall that in BSIM4, the binning check is:\n`lmin <= l < lmax` and `wmin <= w < wmax`\n\n\nSo lmax is exclusive! L=1e-4 is exactly equal to lmax=1e-4, so it fails the check L < Lmax. The issue is specifically with L=100e-6 = Lmax, while W=2e-5 is exactly wmin=2e-5, which should pass since wmin is inclusive. I'll change the bias NMOS and feedback PMOS from l=100e-6 to something smaller like l=50e-6 across the board.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":486,"cache_read_input_tokens":126854,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":486},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"b542c460-f862-414c-9d85-cb131b915b08"}
