{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QUYBtGM8V3nRgcsNEkma9d","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I can see the actual device characteristics:\n- At Vgs=1.0V: Id = 2.44µA (W=20µm, L=20µm)\n- At Vgs=1.5V: Id = 23.6µA\n- At Vgs=2.0V: Id = 65.7µA\n\nThe NFET works fine. The issue is that with a 3MΩ bias resistor and a diode-connected NMOS (W=20µm, L=99µm), the nbias voltage should stabilize around Vgs≈0.9V for ~1µA. But the waveform showed nbias tracking BVDD up to 6V.\n\nThe problem is likely that the L=99µm device (vs L=20µm measured above) conducts much less current. Let me check W=20µm L=99µm."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":529,"cache_read_input_tokens":191042,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":529},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"93b58c34-5119-449f-b9ad-bf80e56d6d78"}
