{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DroPosj9BDHcTCQz7DNH38","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The \"current\" id1 = v(gate)! This is completely wrong. The vector `id1 = (v(pvdd)-v(src))/1` should give the voltage drop across the 1Ω sense resistor, which equals the current. But the values are exactly v(gate).\n\nThis means the sense resistor voltage is v(pvdd)-v(src) = v(gate). That would mean v(src) = v(pvdd) - v(gate) = 5 - Vg. But src should be near pvdd (5V), not at 5-Vg.\n \nLooking at the circuit topology, I think I've found the issue: the PFET's body is connected to pvdd while its source connects through the 1Ω resistor to pvdd, so when the gate voltage is swept below the threshold, the transistor should conduct and pull current from src to ground through the drain. But something about how the source and body are configured seems to be causing the measured current to track the gate voltage instead of behaving like a proper current sense. The model might not be loading correctly, or there's a simulation error happening. I'm wondering if the compatibility mode setting in the initialization file is interfering with how parameters are being interpreted. Let me check whether the initialization file was properly set up after I renamed and recreated it.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":720,"cache_read_input_tokens":347026,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":720},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"84177f96-6807-47d2-b1e8-d8667b250630"}
