{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UksUACBwc7CgtGFCkDMJwS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. Line 49: `XMc1ivn c1inv c1tap gnd gnd sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=60e-6 l=20e-6`\n\nThe NFET has d=c1inv, g=c1tap, s=gnd, b=gnd. This is correct — the gate is c1tap (high impedance).\n\nBut wait, the NFET with W=60µm has a HUGE gate capacitance: Cgs = 2/3 * 60e-6 * 20e-6 * Cox. \n\nThe PFET adds even more gate capacitance to the c1tap node. Combined, the NFET and PFET gates create a total load of about 3.17pF, which is far larger than the 50fF capacitor I added. With the divider's equivalent resistance around 241kΩ, the RC time constant stretches to nearly a microsecond — that's why the transient response is so sluggish even though the standalone divider works fine.\n\nLet me check the math: at t=2.5µs, about 3.3 time constants have elapsed, so c1tap should reach roughly 95% of its steady-state value of 1.50V, giving me around 1.45V. But the simulation shows 0.025V instead, which makes no sense unless the initial conditions are throwing things off. With `uic` enabled, all nodes start at zero, and the divider has to charge c1tap from ground through those resistors — but even accounting for that, the node should be much higher by 2.5µs.\n\nThere's clearly something else draining c1tap. I'm wondering if the gate-drain capacitance of the NFET is the culprit. The drain node (c1inv) is ramping from 0.72V to 1.7V over 3µs, which is a slew rate of about 0.33V/µs. That changing voltage couples through Cgd and pulls current away from c1tap. With a 60µm wide HV NFET, Cgd is substantial, so this capacitive coupling could easily explain the discrepancy.\n\nActually, let me recalculate—even if Cgd is around 0.5pF, the current would only be 0.165nA, which is negligible. So that's not it either.\n\nI'm now suspecting there might be an unintended short path from c1tap to ground, possibly through a naming error or substrate leakage in the resistor. Looking at the resistor model structure, there's a body resistor and parasitic capacitance to the substrate, so I need to trace through the actual connections to see if something's inadvertently tied to ground.\n\nExamining the voltage-dependent body resistance formula and the substrate correction term—with both c1tap and ground at 0V initially, all the voltage differences collapse to zero, so the resistor should just be at its nominal value with no special substrate effects kicking in.\n\nLet me test whether the issue is actually in the subcircuit itself by running a standalone simulation with just the voltage divider and MOSFET gates outside of any subcircuit wrapper. The testbench is passing `gnd` as the ground pin, which maps to node 0 inside the subcircuit, and both the r1 terminal and substrate terminal of the resistor instance are connected to this same ground node—so the connections look correct. I should try adding something to narrow down where the problem actually is.\n\nI'm printing v(xdut.c1tap) in the output and seeing 0.025V, but the standalone test shows 1.50V—a huge difference. Before I go further, I need to check if there's another node also named c1tap hiding inside one of the other subcircuits that might be shadowing the actual node I'm trying to measure. The resistor subcircuit only has r0, r1, sub, t1, t2, and the MOSFET subcircuit only has d, g, s, b, so neither of those is the culprit. I'm going to try a different approach to debug this.\n\nLet me recount the wrdata column assignments to make sure I'm reading the right column for c1tap. I'm verifying the column mappings in my awk command—$8 corresponds to pass_off, $12 to xdut.comp4, and $13 to xdut.c1tap, accounting for the time column at the start of the data. I've been pulling data from the wrong columns this whole time—$8 is actually pass_off, not comp1, and I mislabeled comp4 as c1tap. Let me recalculate with the correct indices.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":393,"cache_read_input_tokens":386092,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":393},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"2d1e23de-1ea0-4c96-842c-7545649ebf39"}
