{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01WMjKV83pcb4KQDznBGP4Jt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"NOW I can see the real data. c1tap IS rising correctly (0.72V → 1.72V as BVDD ramps from 1V to 3.9V). The inverter c1inv transitions from ~5V down to ~0.4V when c1tap crosses the trip point at about c1tap ≈ 1.62V (BVDD ≈ 3.74V).\n\n**c1tap at BVDD=2.5V = 1.08V.** The expected was 1.50V. It's behind because the RC time constant of the divider (with gate loading) causes a lag.\n\nThe divider is responding slowly because the 3.2pF gate capacitance loads it through ~240kΩ. τ = 0.77µs. The ramp is 1V/µs. The c1tap lags BVDD*ratio by about τ * ramp_rate * ratio = 0.77 * 1 * 0.60 = 0.46V.\n\nSo at BVDD=2.5V: c1tap = 2.5*0.60 - 0.46 = 1.04V. Close to measured 1.08V ✓\n\nThe inverter trips at c1tap ≈ 1.62V. Without lag: BVDD_trip = 1.62/0.60 = 2.70V. With lag: BVDD ≈ 2.70 + 0.77µs × 1V/µs = 3.47V. Actual from data: comp1 transitions around BVDD=3.88V. Close to estimate.\n\n**The fix: reduce the gate capacitance on c1tap.** The 60µm NFET has 2.38pF of gate cap. If I reduce to W=20µm: 0.79pF. Total C = 0.79+0.79+0.05 = 1.63pF. τ = 241k × 1.63pF = 0.39µs. Lag = 0.24V. Trip at BVDD ≈ 2.70 + 0.24 = 2.94V. Still late but much better.\n\nEven better: use a LOWER divider resistance. With R_total = 200kΩ (instead of 1MΩ): τ = 48kΩ × 1.63pF = 0.078µs. Lag = 0.05V. Trip at BVDD ≈ 2.75V. Within spec!\n\nBut 200kΩ divider at BVDD=7V: I = 7/200k = 35µA from BVDD. Too much (spec is 20µA total from BVDD). The ladder already uses 7µA. So the comp1 divider budget is 13µA → R_min = 7/13µ = 538kΩ.\n\nWith Rtotal = 600kΩ: τ = 144kΩ × 1.63pF = 0.23µs. Lag = 0.14V. Trip at BVDD ≈ 2.84V. Close to spec (max 2.7V)... still 0.14V over.\n\nAdjust trip target lower: set the divider so trip occurs at BVDD = 2.5 - margin. Use ratio = trip/2.36 where 2.36V is the target with 0.14V lag → trip at 2.50V.\n\nEasier: lower the divider ratio to make c1tap cross the inverter trip earlier. If trip point = 1.52V and I want c1tap = 1.52V at BVDD = 2.36V: ratio = 1.52/2.36 = 0.644.\n\nWith Rtotal = 600kΩ (Ltop + Lbot): Rtop = (1-0.644)*600k = 214kΩ, Rbot = 0.644*600k = 386kΩ.\nLtop = 214k*0.944/2000 + 0.06 = 101µm\nLbot = 386k*0.944/2000 + 0.06 = 182µm\n\nAlso use W=20µm for the NFET (not 60µm) to reduce cap. This shifts the trip point. Let me recalculate the trip for PFET W=20µm, NFET W=20µm:\nTrip ≈ (0.789 + 0.476*(5-1.01))/(1+0.476) = (0.789 + 1.902)/1.476 = 2.691/1.476 = 1.82V\n\nWith W=20µm/20µm trip ≈ 1.82V. Ratio = 1.82/2.5 = 0.728. With lag correction: ~2.5V effective."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1434,"cache_read_input_tokens":389699,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1434},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"7a1fb3f9-b3e7-4280-a8a4-f11cffa23beb"}
