{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Hpu25W2MbhexpqNnhj4bQh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I can see the full picture:\n\n1. **Startup glitch (BVDD 0-0.8V):** comp2-4 briefly go HIGH then return to LOW. This is a POR startup artifact — the bias settling causes a transient.\n\n2. **comp1 fires at BVDD ≈ 2.6V** — within spec (2.3-2.7V) ✓\n3. **comp2 fires at BVDD ≈ 5.9V** — expected 4.2V, late by 1.7V ✗ \n4. **comp3 fires at BVDD ≈ 6.3V** — expected 4.5V, late by 1.8V ✗\n5. **comp4 fires at BVDD ≈ 7.5V** — expected 5.6V, late by 1.9V ✗\n\ncomp1 works! But comp2-4 (PMOS diff pair OTA) are still too slow. This confirms the PMOS diff pair + NMOS mirror architecture is fundamentally limited in speed for these HV devices.\n\nI should convert comp2-4 to the same inverter-based approach as comp1. Let me commit this progress and continue."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2971,"cache_read_input_tokens":401207,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2971},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"2526936f-626a-4250-bf47-99bd407d0a63"}
