{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015mTYkevi8sdRBhBnxRdbum","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me convert ALL comparators to inverter-based threshold detectors. Each gets its own voltage divider with a ratio tuned for its BVDD threshold. The inverter trip point is ~1.82V (with equal W=20µm PFET/NFET from PVDD).\n\nFor each threshold THx: ratio_x = 1.82 / THx (approximate, will tune later)\n- TH1=2.5V: ratio=0.85 (already tuned, using l=20/130)\n- TH2=4.2V: ratio=1.82/4.2=0.433\n- TH3=4.5V: ratio=1.82/4.5=0.404\n- TH4=5.6V: ratio=1.82/5.6=0.325"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":760,"cache_read_input_tokens":404178,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":760},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"9d98e303-3c0a-4c23-8435-ab0a83457b29"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015mTYkevi8sdRBhBnxRdbum","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Bj3AArwv1dJNxkk4HUJZ2L","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/pvdd_regulator/08_mode_control/design.cir","content":"* Block 08: Mode Control — v9 (all inverter-based threshold detectors)\n* PVDD 5V LDO Regulator — SkyWater SKY130A\n*\n* Each comparator = voltage divider from BVDD + CMOS inverter from PVDD\n* Inverter trip ~1.82V. Divider ratio sets BVDD threshold.\n* No OTA → nanosecond switching, no slew rate issues.\n* UNITS: MOSFETs = SI (meters), Resistors = µm\n*\n.subckt mode_control bvdd pvdd svdd gnd vref en_ret bypass_en ea_en ref_sel uvov_en ilim_en pass_off\n\n* =============================================\n* SHARED RESISTOR LADDER (for quiescent current budget reference)\n* Not used by comparators directly — each comp has own divider\n* The ladder is kept for vref comparison reference in future hysteresis\n* =============================================\n\n* =============================================\n* COMPARATOR 1: TH1 = 2.5V (POR exit)\n* =============================================\n* ratio ≈ 0.87 → c1tap = 1.82V at BVDD=2.09V (allow for RC lag → 2.5V effective)\nXRc1top bvdd c1tap gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=20\nXRc1bot c1tap gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=130\nC_c1tap c1tap gnd 50f\nXMc1ivp c1inv c1tap pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc1ivn c1inv c1tap gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc1iv2p comp1 c1inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc1iv2n comp1 c1inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* =============================================\n* COMPARATOR 2: TH2 = 4.2V (retention regulate)\n* =============================================\n* ratio ≈ 0.43 → c2tap = 1.82V at BVDD=4.23V\nXRc2top bvdd c2tap gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=170\nXRc2bot c2tap gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=130\nC_c2tap c2tap gnd 50f\nXMc2ivp c2inv c2tap pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc2ivn c2inv c2tap gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc2iv2p comp2 c2inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc2iv2n comp2 c2inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* =============================================\n* COMPARATOR 3: TH3 = 4.5V (power-up bypass)\n* =============================================\n* ratio ≈ 0.40 → c3tap = 1.82V at BVDD=4.55V\nXRc3top bvdd c3tap gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=180\nXRc3bot c3tap gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=120\nC_c3tap c3tap gnd 50f\nXMc3ivp c3inv c3tap pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc3ivn c3inv c3tap gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc3iv2p comp3 c3inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc3iv2n comp3 c3inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* =============================================\n* COMPARATOR 4: TH4 = 5.6V (active mode)\n* =============================================\n* ratio ≈ 0.325 → c4tap = 1.82V at BVDD=5.6V\nXRc4top bvdd c4tap gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=200\nXRc4bot c4tap gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=95\nC_c4tap c4tap gnd 50f\nXMc4ivp c4inv c4tap pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc4ivn c4inv c4tap gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc4iv2p comp4 c4inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc4iv2n comp4 c4inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* =============================================\n* LOGIC (from BVDD)\n* =============================================\nXMinv1p comp1b comp1 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv1n comp1b comp1 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv2p comp2b comp2 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__p