{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01V4f1qxf3Ag1Ft6cUgw7kz3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"NOW the correct results:\n- **comp1: BVDD=2.68V** (target 2.5V, spec 2.3-2.7V) — just barely above max, off by 0.01V\n- **comp2: BVDD=5.33V** (target 4.2V, spec 4.0-4.4V) — 1.1V late ✗\n- **comp3: BVDD=5.69V** (target 4.5V, spec 4.3-4.7V) — 1.2V late ✗\n- **comp4: BVDD=6.91V** (target 5.6V, spec 5.4-5.8V) — 1.3V late ✗\n\ncomp2-4 are still late due to RC lag from the high-impedance dividers. The issue: the gate capacitance (~1.6pF) on each tap causes the divider response to lag the BVDD ramp.\n\nThe fix: **lower the divider impedance** to reduce τ. For comp2-4, I can use shorter resistors (lower R_total). At BVDD=7V, the current from all 4 dividers + logic must be < 20µA.\n\ncomp1 divider: l=20+130=150µm → R≈300kΩ → I_at_7V = 7/300k = 23µA. Already over budget alone!\n\nI need to rethink the BVDD current budget. The divider current adds to Iq. With 4 dividers at 300kΩ each: total = 4 × 7/300k = 93µA. Way over 20µA.\n\nFor total Iq < 20µA from BVDD at 7V: total R ≥ 7V/20µA = 350kΩ. If I use one shared divider with 4 taps (like the original ladder), the current is shared.\n\nLet me go back to the **shared ladder + individual inverters** approach. The shared ladder provides 4 tap points, each feeding a PVDD-powered CMOS inverter. The inverter trip matches each tap at its target BVDD.\n\nThe key difference from the original: each comparator's inverter can have DIFFERENT sizing to set different trip points, matching each tap's voltage at its threshold BVDD."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":275,"cache_read_input_tokens":417480,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":275},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"ab532b3a-9d97-467f-9e59-0215a83355da"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01V4f1qxf3Ag1Ft6cUgw7kz3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Nbb9ac4dX7Cj1dTnvQWgw9","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/pvdd_regulator/08_mode_control/design.cir","content":"* Block 08: Mode Control — v10 (shared ladder + PVDD inverters)\n* PVDD 5V LDO Regulator — SkyWater SKY130A\n*\n* Shared resistor ladder from BVDD to GND (1MΩ total, ~7µA at 7V)\n* Each tap feeds a PVDD-powered CMOS inverter with customized sizing\n* so trip point matches tap voltage at the target BVDD threshold.\n*\n* Inverter trip = f(Wp/Wn). Match to tap(THx):\n*   tap1 at TH1=2.5V: tap1 = 2.5*0.49 = 1.226V → need trip=1.226V\n*   tap2 at TH2=4.2V: tap2 = 4.2*0.29 = 1.219V → need trip≈1.22V\n*   tap3 at TH3=4.5V: tap3 = 4.5*0.27 = 1.215V → need trip≈1.22V\n*   tap4 at TH4=5.6V: tap4 = 5.6*0.22 = 1.232V → need trip≈1.23V\n*\n* All taps cross ~1.22V! The trips are all the same! Just use inverters\n* with trip≈1.22V (PVDD=5V). Need strong NFET / weak PFET.\n*\n* For trip=1.22V with PVDD=5V:\n*   (Vtn + k*(PVDD+Vtp))/(1+k) = 1.22\n*   (0.789 + k*(5-1.01))/(1+k) = 1.22\n*   0.789 + 3.99*k = 1.22 + 1.22*k\n*   2.77*k = 0.431\n*   k = sqrt(Bp/Bn) = 0.156\n*   Bp/Bn = 0.024\n* This requires NFET ~40x stronger than PFET. Min W=20µm for both.\n* With Wp=20, Wn=20: Bp/Bn = up/un ≈ 0.23 → trip ≈ 1.93V. Too high.\n* Cannot achieve trip=1.22V with minimum-size devices.\n*\n* Alternative: use vref as the inverter reference instead of GND.\n* Pseudo-NMOS: PFET pull-up from PVDD, NFET with gate=tap and source=vref.\n* NFET turns ON when tap > vref + Vth. But Vth≈0.789V: trip at tap=2.02V ≠ 1.22V.\n*\n* Better: use a differential pair approach — but we already tried that.\n*\n* SIMPLEST SOLUTION: use vref as the NFET source in each inverter.\n* When tap > vref: NFET ON (Vgs > Vth) → output LOW → comp=HIGH (after inv)\n* Trip at tap = vref + Vth_n. But Vth≈0.789V → trip at 2.015V, not 1.22V.\n*\n* Wait — what about this: use NFET with source at a tap-dependent voltage?\n* Or: connect NFET source to the tap from the NEXT lower comparator?\n*\n* Actually, the REAL solution: just connect the shared ladder taps to\n* PVDD-powered inverters, and accept that the trip is at 1.93V.\n* Then adjust the ladder ratios so that each tap reaches 1.93V at the\n* desired BVDD threshold.\n*\n* New ladder ratios:\n*   tap1 = 1.93V when BVDD = 2.5V → ratio1 = 1.93/2.5 = 0.772\n*   tap2 = 1.93V when BVDD = 4.2V → ratio2 = 1.93/4.2 = 0.4595\n*   tap3 = 1.93V when BVDD = 4.5V → ratio3 = 1.93/4.5 = 0.4289\n*   tap4 = 1.93V when BVDD = 5.6V → ratio4 = 1.93/5.6 = 0.3446\n*\n* Check: ratio1 > ratio2 > ratio3 > ratio4 → 0.772 > 0.460 > 0.429 > 0.345 ✓\n*\n* Ladder resistor ratios:\n*   Rbot/Rtot = ratio4 = 0.345\n*   (R34+Rbot)/Rtot = ratio3 = 0.429 → R34/Rtot = 0.084\n*   (R23+R34+Rbot)/Rtot = ratio2 = 0.460 → R23/Rtot = 0.031\n*   (R12+R23+R34+Rbot)/Rtot = ratio1 = 0.772 → R12/Rtot = 0.312\n*   Rtop/Rtot = 1-0.772 = 0.228\n*\n* With Rtotal = 1MΩ (l_total ≈ 475µm): I_BVDD = BVDD/1M = 7µA at 7V ✓\n*   Rbot: 0.345 → l = 0.345*475 = 163µm\n*   R34:  0.084 → l = 0.084*475 = 40µm\n*   R23:  0.031 → l = 0.031*475 = 15µm\n*   R12:  0.312 → l = 0.312*475 = 148µm\n*   Rtop: 0.228 → l = 0.228*475 = 108µm\n*\n.subckt mode_control bvdd pvdd svdd gnd vref en_ret bypass_en ea_en ref_sel uvov_en ilim_en pass_off\n\n* =============================================\n* RESISTOR LADDER\n* =============================================\nXRtop bvdd tap1 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=108\nXR12  tap1 tap2 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=148\nXR23  tap2 tap3 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=15\nXR34  tap3 tap4 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=40\nXRbot tap4 gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=163\nC_tap1 tap1 gnd 100f\nC_tap2 tap2 gnd 100f\nC_tap3 tap3 gnd 100f\nC_tap4 tap4 gnd 100f\n\n* =============================================\n* COMPARATORS: PVDD-powered inverters on each tap\n* Trip point ≈ 1.93V for W_p=W_n=20µm\n* =============================================\n\n* COMP1: tap1 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp1\nXMc1ivp c1inv tap1 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc1ivn c1inv tap1 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc1iv2p comp1 c1inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc1iv2n comp1 c1inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* COMP2: tap2 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp2\nXMc2ivp c2inv tap2 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc2ivn c2inv tap2 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc2iv2p comp2 c2inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc2iv2n comp2 c2inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* COMP3: tap3 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp3\nXMc3ivp c3inv tap3 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc3ivn c3inv tap3 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc3iv2p comp3 c3inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc3iv2n comp3 c3inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* COMP4: tap4 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp4\nXMc4ivp c4inv tap4 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc4ivn c4inv tap4 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc4iv2p comp4 c4inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc4iv2n comp4 c4inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* =============================================\n* LOGIC (from BVDD)\n* =============================================\nXMinv1p comp1b comp1 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv1n comp1b comp1 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv2p comp2b comp2 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv2n comp2b comp2 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv3p comp3b comp3 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv3n comp3b comp3 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv4p comp4b comp4 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv4n comp4b comp4 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXRpo_pu bvdd pass_off gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=50\nXMpo_bufp pass_off comp1b bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMpo_bufn pass_off comp1b gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXMby_n1a by_s1     comp1  gnd gnd sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_n1b bypass_enb comp2b by_s1 by_s1 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_n2a by_s2     comp3  gnd gnd sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_n2b bypass_enb comp4b by_s2 by_s2 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_p1a by_pmid comp1  bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_p1b by_pmid comp2b bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_p2a bypass_enb comp3  by_pmid by_pmid sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_p2b bypass_enb comp4b by_pmid by_pmid sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_outp bypass_en bypass_enb bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_outn bypass_en bypass_enb gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXMea_n1a ea_s1  comp2  gnd gnd sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_n1b ea_enb comp3b ea_s1 ea_s1 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_n2  ea_enb comp4  gnd gnd sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_p1a ea_pmid comp2  bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_p1b ea_pmid comp3b bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_p2  ea_enb  comp4  ea_pmid ea_pmid sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_outp ea_en ea_enb bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_outn ea_en ea_enb gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXMrs_n1 rs_s1    comp1  gnd gnd sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMrs_n2 ref_selb comp3b rs_s1 rs_s1 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMrs_p1 ref_selb comp1  bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMrs_p2 ref_selb comp3b bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMrs_outp ref_sel ref_selb bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMrs_outn ref_sel ref_selb gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXMuv_p1 uvov_enb comp4 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMuv_n1 uvov_enb comp4 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMuv_p2 uvov_en uvov_enb bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMuv_n2 uvov_en uvov_enb gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXMil_p1 ilim_enb comp4 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMil_n1 ilim_enb comp4 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMil_p2 ilim_en ilim_enb bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMil_n2 ilim_en ilim_enb gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n.ends mode_control\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":275,"cache_read_input_tokens":417480,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":275},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"14642b13-04ff-48d9-ac5d-9e781a1cde56"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Nbb9ac4dX7Cj1dTnvQWgw9","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/pvdd_regulator/08_mode_control/design.cir has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"e229e562-92bd-45f9-85d4-52804d7734a1","timestamp":"2026-03-29T16:44:26.294Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/pvdd_regulator/08_mode_control/design.cir","content":"* Block 08: Mode Control — v10 (shared ladder + PVDD inverters)\n* PVDD 5V LDO Regulator — SkyWater SKY130A\n*\n* Shared resistor ladder from BVDD to GND (1MΩ total, ~7µA at 7V)\n* Each tap feeds a PVDD-powered CMOS inverter with customized sizing\n* so trip point matches tap voltage at the target BVDD threshold.\n*\n* Inverter trip = f(Wp/Wn). Match to tap(THx):\n*   tap1 at TH1=2.5V: tap1 = 2.5*0.49 = 1.226V → need trip=1.226V\n*   tap2 at TH2=4.2V: tap2 = 4.2*0.29 = 1.219V → need trip≈1.22V\n*   tap3 at TH3=4.5V: tap3 = 4.5*0.27 = 1.215V → need trip≈1.22V\n*   tap4 at TH4=5.6V: tap4 = 5.6*0.22 = 1.232V → need trip≈1.23V\n*\n* All taps cross ~1.22V! The trips are all the same! Just use inverters\n* with trip≈1.22V (PVDD=5V). Need strong NFET / weak PFET.\n*\n* For trip=1.22V with PVDD=5V:\n*   (Vtn + k*(PVDD+Vtp))/(1+k) = 1.22\n*   (0.789 + k*(5-1.01))/(1+k) = 1.22\n*   0.789 + 3.99*k = 1.22 + 1.22*k\n*   2.77*k = 0.431\n*   k = sqrt(Bp/Bn) = 0.156\n*   Bp/Bn = 0.024\n* This requires NFET ~40x stronger than PFET. Min W=20µm for both.\n* With Wp=20, Wn=20: Bp/Bn = up/un ≈ 0.23 → trip ≈ 1.93V. Too high.\n* Cannot achieve trip=1.22V with minimum-size devices.\n*\n* Alternative: use vref as the inverter reference instead of GND.\n* Pseudo-NMOS: PFET pull-up from PVDD, NFET with gate=tap and source=vref.\n* NFET turns ON when tap > vref + Vth. But Vth≈0.789V: trip at tap=2.02V ≠ 1.22V.\n*\n* Better: use a differential pair approach — but we already tried that.\n*\n* SIMPLEST SOLUTION: use vref as the NFET source in each inverter.\n* When tap > vref: NFET ON (Vgs > Vth) → output LOW → comp=HIGH (after inv)\n* Trip at tap = vref + Vth_n. But Vth≈0.789V → trip at 2.015V, not 1.22V.\n*\n* Wait — what about this: use NFET with source at a tap-dependent voltage?\n* Or: connect NFET source to the tap from the NEXT lower comparator?\n*\n* Actually, the REAL solution: just connect the shared ladder taps to\n* PVDD-powered inverters, and accept that the trip is at 1.93V.\n* Then adjust the ladder ratios so that each tap reaches 1.93V at the\n* desired BVDD threshold.\n*\n* New ladder ratios:\n*   tap1 = 1.93V when BVDD = 2.5V → ratio1 = 1.93/2.5 = 0.772\n*   tap2 = 1.93V when BVDD = 4.2V → ratio2 = 1.93/4.2 = 0.4595\n*   tap3 = 1.93V when BVDD = 4.5V → ratio3 = 1.93/4.5 = 0.4289\n*   tap4 = 1.93V when BVDD = 5.6V → ratio4 = 1.93/5.6 = 0.3446\n*\n* Check: ratio1 > ratio2 > ratio3 > ratio4 → 0.772 > 0.460 > 0.429 > 0.345 ✓\n*\n* Ladder resistor ratios:\n*   Rbot/Rtot = ratio4 = 0.345\n*   (R34+Rbot)/Rtot = ratio3 = 0.429 → R34/Rtot = 0.084\n*   (R23+R34+Rbot)/Rtot = ratio2 = 0.460 → R23/Rtot = 0.031\n*   (R12+R23+R34+Rbot)/Rtot = ratio1 = 0.772 → R12/Rtot = 0.312\n*   Rtop/Rtot = 1-0.772 = 0.228\n*\n* With Rtotal = 1MΩ (l_total ≈ 475µm): I_BVDD = BVDD/1M = 7µA at 7V ✓\n*   Rbot: 0.345 → l = 0.345*475 = 163µm\n*   R34:  0.084 → l = 0.084*475 = 40µm\n*   R23:  0.031 → l = 0.031*475 = 15µm\n*   R12:  0.312 → l = 0.312*475 = 148µm\n*   Rtop: 0.228 → l = 0.228*475 = 108µm\n*\n.subckt mode_control bvdd pvdd svdd gnd vref en_ret bypass_en ea_en ref_sel uvov_en ilim_en pass_off\n\n* =============================================\n* RESISTOR LADDER\n* =============================================\nXRtop bvdd tap1 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=108\nXR12  tap1 tap2 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=148\nXR23  tap2 tap3 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=15\nXR34  tap3 tap4 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=40\nXRbot tap4 gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=163\nC_tap1 tap1 gnd 100f\nC_tap2 tap2 gnd 100f\nC_tap3 tap3 gnd 100f\nC_tap4 tap4 gnd 100f\n\n* =============================================\n* COMPARATORS: PVDD-powered inverters on each tap\n* Trip point ≈ 1.93V for W_p=W_n=20µm\n* =============================================\n\n* COMP1: tap1 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp1\nXMc1ivp c1inv tap1 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc1ivn c1inv tap1 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc1iv2p comp1 c1inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc1iv2n comp1 c1inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* COMP2: tap2 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp2\nXMc2ivp c2inv tap2 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc2ivn c2inv tap2 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc2iv2p comp2 c2inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc2iv2n comp2 c2inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* COMP3: tap3 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp3\nXMc3ivp c3inv tap3 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc3ivn c3inv tap3 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc3iv2p comp3 c3inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc3iv2n comp3 c3inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* COMP4: tap4 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp4\nXMc4ivp c4inv tap4 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc4ivn c4inv tap4 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc4iv2p comp4 c4inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc4iv2n comp4 c4inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* =============================================\n* LOGIC (from BVDD)\n* =============================================\nXMinv1p comp1b comp1 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv1n comp1b comp1 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv2p comp2b comp2 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv2n comp2b comp2 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv3p comp3b comp3 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv3n comp3b comp3 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv4p comp4b comp4 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv4n comp4b comp4 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXRpo_pu bvdd pass_off gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=50\nXMpo_bufp pass_off comp1b bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMpo_bufn pass_off comp1b gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXMby_n1a by_s1     comp1  gnd gnd sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_n1b bypass_enb comp2b by_s1 by_s1 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_n2a by_s2     comp3  gnd gnd sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_n2b bypass_enb comp4b by_s2 by_s2 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_p1a by_pmid comp1  bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_p1b by_pmid comp2b bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_p2a bypass_enb comp3  by_pmid by_pmid sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_p2b bypass_enb comp4b by_pmid by_pmid sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_outp bypass_en bypass_enb bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMby_outn bypass_en bypass_enb gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXMea_n1a ea_s1  comp2  gnd gnd sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_n1b ea_enb comp3b ea_s1 ea_s1 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_n2  ea_enb comp4  gnd gnd sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_p1a ea_pmid comp2  bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_p1b ea_pmid comp3b bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_p2  ea_enb  comp4  ea_pmid ea_pmid sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_outp ea_en ea_enb bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMea_outn ea_en ea_enb gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXMrs_n1 rs_s1    comp1  gnd gnd sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMrs_n2 ref_selb comp3b rs_s1 rs_s1 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMrs_p1 ref_selb comp1  bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMrs_p2 ref_selb comp3b bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMrs_outp ref_sel ref_selb bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMrs_outn ref_sel ref_selb gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXMuv_p1 uvov_enb comp4 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMuv_n1 uvov_enb comp4 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMuv_p2 uvov_en uvov_enb bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMuv_n2 uvov_en uvov_enb gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXMil_p1 ilim_enb comp4 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMil_n1 ilim_enb comp4 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMil_p2 ilim_en ilim_enb bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMil_n2 ilim_en ilim_enb gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n.ends mode_control\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":64,"newStart":1,"newLines":111,"lines":["-* Block 08: Mode Control — v9 (all inverter-based threshold detectors)","+* Block 08: Mode Control — v10 (shared ladder + PVDD inverters)"," * PVDD 5V LDO Regulator — SkyWater SKY130A"," *","-* Each comparator = voltage divider from BVDD + CMOS inverter from PVDD","-* Inverter trip ~1.82V. Divider ratio sets BVDD threshold.","-* No OTA → nanosecond switching, no slew rate issues.","-* UNITS: MOSFETs = SI (meters), Resistors = µm","+* Shared resistor ladder from BVDD to GND (1MΩ total, ~7µA at 7V)","+* Each tap feeds a PVDD-powered CMOS inverter with customized sizing","+* so trip point matches tap voltage at the target BVDD threshold."," *","+* Inverter trip = f(Wp/Wn). Match to tap(THx):","+*   tap1 at TH1=2.5V: tap1 = 2.5*0.49 = 1.226V → need trip=1.226V","+*   tap2 at TH2=4.2V: tap2 = 4.2*0.29 = 1.219V → need trip≈1.22V","+*   tap3 at TH3=4.5V: tap3 = 4.5*0.27 = 1.215V → need trip≈1.22V","+*   tap4 at TH4=5.6V: tap4 = 5.6*0.22 = 1.232V → need trip≈1.23V","+*","+* All taps cross ~1.22V! The trips are all the same! Just use inverters","+* with trip≈1.22V (PVDD=5V). Need strong NFET / weak PFET.","+*","+* For trip=1.22V with PVDD=5V:","+*   (Vtn + k*(PVDD+Vtp))/(1+k) = 1.22","+*   (0.789 + k*(5-1.01))/(1+k) = 1.22","+*   0.789 + 3.99*k = 1.22 + 1.22*k","+*   2.77*k = 0.431","+*   k = sqrt(Bp/Bn) = 0.156","+*   Bp/Bn = 0.024","+* This requires NFET ~40x stronger than PFET. Min W=20µm for both.","+* With Wp=20, Wn=20: Bp/Bn = up/un ≈ 0.23 → trip ≈ 1.93V. Too high.","+* Cannot achieve trip=1.22V with minimum-size devices.","+*","+* Alternative: use vref as the inverter reference instead of GND.","+* Pseudo-NMOS: PFET pull-up from PVDD, NFET with gate=tap and source=vref.","+* NFET turns ON when tap > vref + Vth. But Vth≈0.789V: trip at tap=2.02V ≠ 1.22V.","+*","+* Better: use a differential pair approach — but we already tried that.","+*","+* SIMPLEST SOLUTION: use vref as the NFET source in each inverter.","+* When tap > vref: NFET ON (Vgs > Vth) → output LOW → comp=HIGH (after inv)","+* Trip at tap = vref + Vth_n. But Vth≈0.789V → trip at 2.015V, not 1.22V.","+*","+* Wait — what about this: use NFET with source at a tap-dependent voltage?","+* Or: connect NFET source to the tap from the NEXT lower comparator?","+*","+* Actually, the REAL solution: just connect the shared ladder taps to","+* PVDD-powered inverters, and accept that the trip is at 1.93V.","+* Then adjust the ladder ratios so that each tap reaches 1.93V at the","+* desired BVDD threshold.","+*","+* New ladder ratios:","+*   tap1 = 1.93V when BVDD = 2.5V → ratio1 = 1.93/2.5 = 0.772","+*   tap2 = 1.93V when BVDD = 4.2V → ratio2 = 1.93/4.2 = 0.4595","+*   tap3 = 1.93V when BVDD = 4.5V → ratio3 = 1.93/4.5 = 0.4289","+*   tap4 = 1.93V when BVDD = 5.6V → ratio4 = 1.93/5.6 = 0.3446","+*","+* Check: ratio1 > ratio2 > ratio3 > ratio4 → 0.772 > 0.460 > 0.429 > 0.345 ✓","+*","+* Ladder resistor ratios:","+*   Rbot/Rtot = ratio4 = 0.345","+*   (R34+Rbot)/Rtot = ratio3 = 0.429 → R34/Rtot = 0.084","+*   (R23+R34+Rbot)/Rtot = ratio2 = 0.460 → R23/Rtot = 0.031","+*   (R12+R23+R34+Rbot)/Rtot = ratio1 = 0.772 → R12/Rtot = 0.312","+*   Rtop/Rtot = 1-0.772 = 0.228","+*","+* With Rtotal = 1MΩ (l_total ≈ 475µm): I_BVDD = BVDD/1M = 7µA at 7V ✓","+*   Rbot: 0.345 → l = 0.345*475 = 163µm","+*   R34:  0.084 → l = 0.084*475 = 40µm","+*   R23:  0.031 → l = 0.031*475 = 15µm","+*   R12:  0.312 → l = 0.312*475 = 148µm","+*   Rtop: 0.228 → l = 0.228*475 = 108µm","+*"," .subckt mode_control bvdd pvdd svdd gnd vref en_ret bypass_en ea_en ref_sel uvov_en ilim_en pass_off"," "," * =============================================","-* SHARED RESISTOR LADDER (for quiescent current budget reference)","-* Not used by comparators directly — each comp has own divider","-* The ladder is kept for vref comparison reference in future hysteresis","+* RESISTOR LADDER"," * =============================================","+XRtop bvdd tap1 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=108","+XR12  tap1 tap2 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=148","+XR23  tap2 tap3 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=15","+XR34  tap3 tap4 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=40","+XRbot tap4 gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=163","+C_tap1 tap1 gnd 100f","+C_tap2 tap2 gnd 100f","+C_tap3 tap3 gnd 100f","+C_tap4 tap4 gnd 100f"," "," * =============================================","-* COMPARATOR 1: TH1 = 2.5V (POR exit)","+* COMPARATORS: PVDD-powered inverters on each tap","+* Trip point ≈ 1.93V for W_p=W_n=20µm"," * =============================================","-* ratio ≈ 0.87 → c1tap = 1.82V at BVDD=2.09V (allow for RC lag → 2.5V effective)","-XRc1top bvdd c1tap gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=20","-XRc1bot c1tap gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=130","-C_c1tap c1tap gnd 50f","-XMc1ivp c1inv c1tap pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6","-XMc1ivn c1inv c1tap gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6","+","+* COMP1: tap1 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp1","+XMc1ivp c1inv tap1 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6","+XMc1ivn c1inv tap1 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6"," XMc1iv2p comp1 c1inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6"," XMc1iv2n comp1 c1inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6"," ","-* =============================================","-* COMPARATOR 2: TH2 = 4.2V (retention regulate)","-* =============================================","-* ratio ≈ 0.43 → c2tap = 1.82V at BVDD=4.23V","-XRc2top bvdd c2tap gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=170","-XRc2bot c2tap gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=130","-C_c2tap c2tap gnd 50f","-XMc2ivp c2inv c2tap pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6","-XMc2ivn c2inv c2tap gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6","+* COMP2: tap2 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp2","+XMc2ivp c2inv tap2 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6","+XMc2ivn c2inv tap2 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6"," XMc2iv2p comp2 c2inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6"," XMc2iv2n comp2 c2inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6"," ","-* =============================================","-* COMPARATOR 3: TH3 = 4.5V (power-up bypass)","-* =============================================","-* ratio ≈ 0.40 → c3tap = 1.82V at BVDD=4.55V","-XRc3top bvdd c3tap gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=180","-XRc3bot c3tap gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=120","-C_c3tap c3tap gnd 50f","-XMc3ivp c3inv c3tap pvdd p