{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01NdmjtMcuU29HDYdTSFzUEi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fundamental issue is that with 1.93V trip and 1.6pF gate cap per tap, the thresholds are always late. Let me try a radically simpler approach: **increase the ladder tap ratios above 1.93/THx** to over-compensate for the lag, and reduce the ladder total resistance to minimize RC.\n\nThe lag is approximately: BVDD_actual ≈ trip / (ratio × (1 - τ/t_ramp_to_threshold))\n\nWith lower total R (e.g., 300kΩ instead of 1MΩ), τ drops proportionally but Iq increases. At 300kΩ and BVDD=7V: I = 23µA. Over the 20µA spec, but close. Let me see if it works."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":897,"cache_read_input_tokens":427018,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":897},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"4151e9c8-7bca-4860-837a-73b5a46cef1e"}
