{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01L8uLRAaqxJWM8a1txeU8tx","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/pvdd_regulator/08_mode_control/design.cir has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"9f6e1458-4d14-4f5c-a580-d80775b1569e","timestamp":"2026-03-29T16:46:16.909Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/pvdd_regulator/08_mode_control/design.cir","oldString":"* Ladder scaled to ~300kΩ total (lower RC) with higher ratios to compensate lag\n* ratio1=0.85, ratio2=0.52, ratio3=0.49, ratio4=0.40\n* Rbot = 0.40*142 = 57µm, R34 = 0.09*142 = 13µm\n* R23 = 0.03*142 = 4.3µm (too short, use min ~5), R12 = 0.33*142 = 47µm\n* Rtop = 0.15*142 = 21µm\nXRtop bvdd tap1 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=21\nXR12  tap1 tap2 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=47\nXR23  tap2 tap3 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=5\nXR34  tap3 tap4 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=13\nXRbot tap4 gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=57","newString":"* Ladder ~300kΩ, boosted ratios to compensate 12% RC lag\n* Desired: trip at 1.93V. Need tap_ss at threshold to be 1.93V/0.88 ≈ 2.19V\n* New ratios (1.12× of theoretical): r1=0.87, r2=0.52, r3=0.48, r4=0.39\nXRtop bvdd tap1 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=18\nXR12  tap1 tap2 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=50\nXR23  tap2 tap3 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=6\nXR34  tap3 tap4 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=12\nXRbot tap4 gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=56","originalFile":"* Block 08: Mode Control — v10 (shared ladder + PVDD inverters)\n* PVDD 5V LDO Regulator — SkyWater SKY130A\n*\n* Shared resistor ladder from BVDD to GND (1MΩ total, ~7µA at 7V)\n* Each tap feeds a PVDD-powered CMOS inverter with customized sizing\n* so trip point matches tap voltage at the target BVDD threshold.\n*\n* Inverter trip = f(Wp/Wn). Match to tap(THx):\n*   tap1 at TH1=2.5V: tap1 = 2.5*0.49 = 1.226V → need trip=1.226V\n*   tap2 at TH2=4.2V: tap2 = 4.2*0.29 = 1.219V → need trip≈1.22V\n*   tap3 at TH3=4.5V: tap3 = 4.5*0.27 = 1.215V → need trip≈1.22V\n*   tap4 at TH4=5.6V: tap4 = 5.6*0.22 = 1.232V → need trip≈1.23V\n*\n* All taps cross ~1.22V! The trips are all the same! Just use inverters\n* with trip≈1.22V (PVDD=5V). Need strong NFET / weak PFET.\n*\n* For trip=1.22V with PVDD=5V:\n*   (Vtn + k*(PVDD+Vtp))/(1+k) = 1.22\n*   (0.789 + k*(5-1.01))/(1+k) = 1.22\n*   0.789 + 3.99*k = 1.22 + 1.22*k\n*   2.77*k = 0.431\n*   k = sqrt(Bp/Bn) = 0.156\n*   Bp/Bn = 0.024\n* This requires NFET ~40x stronger than PFET. Min W=20µm for both.\n* With Wp=20, Wn=20: Bp/Bn = up/un ≈ 0.23 → trip ≈ 1.93V. Too high.\n* Cannot achieve trip=1.22V with minimum-size devices.\n*\n* Alternative: use vref as the inverter reference instead of GND.\n* Pseudo-NMOS: PFET pull-up from PVDD, NFET with gate=tap and source=vref.\n* NFET turns ON when tap > vref + Vth. But Vth≈0.789V: trip at tap=2.02V ≠ 1.22V.\n*\n* Better: use a differential pair approach — but we already tried that.\n*\n* SIMPLEST SOLUTION: use vref as the NFET source in each inverter.\n* When tap > vref: NFET ON (Vgs > Vth) → output LOW → comp=HIGH (after inv)\n* Trip at tap = vref + Vth_n. But Vth≈0.789V → trip at 2.015V, not 1.22V.\n*\n* Wait — what about this: use NFET with source at a tap-dependent voltage?\n* Or: connect NFET source to the tap from the NEXT lower comparator?\n*\n* Actually, the REAL solution: just connect the shared ladder taps to\n* PVDD-powered inverters, and accept that the trip is at 1.93V.\n* Then adjust the ladder ratios so that each tap reaches 1.93V at the\n* desired BVDD threshold.\n*\n* New ladder ratios:\n*   tap1 = 1.93V when BVDD = 2.5V → ratio1 = 1.93/2.5 = 0.772\n*   tap2 = 1.93V when BVDD = 4.2V → ratio2 = 1.93/4.2 = 0.4595\n*   tap3 = 1.93V when BVDD = 4.5V → ratio3 = 1.93/4.5 = 0.4289\n*   tap4 = 1.93V when BVDD = 5.6V → ratio4 = 1.93/5.6 = 0.3446\n*\n* Check: ratio1 > ratio2 > ratio3 > ratio4 → 0.772 > 0.460 > 0.429 > 0.345 ✓\n*\n* Ladder resistor ratios:\n*   Rbot/Rtot = ratio4 = 0.345\n*   (R34+Rbot)/Rtot = ratio3 = 0.429 → R34/Rtot = 0.084\n*   (R23+R34+Rbot)/Rtot = ratio2 = 0.460 → R23/Rtot = 0.031\n*   (R12+R23+R34+Rbot)/Rtot = ratio1 = 0.772 → R12/Rtot = 0.312\n*   Rtop/Rtot = 1-0.772 = 0.228\n*\n* With Rtotal = 1MΩ (l_total ≈ 475µm): I_BVDD = BVDD/1M = 7µA at 7V ✓\n*   Rbot: 0.345 → l = 0.345*475 = 163µm\n*   R34:  0.084 → l = 0.084*475 = 40µm\n*   R23:  0.031 → l = 0.031*475 = 15µm\n*   R12:  0.312 → l = 0.312*475 = 148µm\n*   Rtop: 0.228 → l = 0.228*475 = 108µm\n*\n.subckt mode_control bvdd pvdd svdd gnd vref en_ret bypass_en ea_en ref_sel uvov_en ilim_en pass_off\n\n* =============================================\n* RESISTOR LADDER\n* =============================================\n* Ladder scaled to ~300kΩ total (lower RC) with higher ratios to compensate lag\n* ratio1=0.85, ratio2=0.52, ratio3=0.49, ratio4=0.40\n* Rbot = 0.40*142 = 57µm, R34 = 0.09*142 = 13µm\n* R23 = 0.03*142 = 4.3µm (too short, use min ~5), R12 = 0.33*142 = 47µm\n* Rtop = 0.15*142 = 21µm\nXRtop bvdd tap1 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=21\nXR12  tap1 tap2 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=47\nXR23  tap2 tap3 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=5\nXR34  tap3 tap4 gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=13\nXRbot tap4 gnd  gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=57\nC_tap1 tap1 gnd 100f\nC_tap2 tap2 gnd 100f\nC_tap3 tap3 gnd 100f\nC_tap4 tap4 gnd 100f\n\n* =============================================\n* COMPARATORS: PVDD-powered inverters on each tap\n* Trip point ≈ 1.93V for W_p=W_n=20µm\n* =============================================\n\n* COMP1: tap1 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp1\nXMc1ivp c1inv tap1 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc1ivn c1inv tap1 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc1iv2p comp1 c1inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc1iv2n comp1 c1inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* COMP2: tap2 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp2\nXMc2ivp c2inv tap2 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc2ivn c2inv tap2 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc2iv2p comp2 c2inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc2iv2n comp2 c2inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* COMP3: tap3 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp3\nXMc3ivp c3inv tap3 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc3ivn c3inv tap3 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc3iv2p comp3 c3inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc3iv2n comp3 c3inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* COMP4: tap4 → inverter → 2nd inverter → comp4\nXMc4ivp c4inv tap4 pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc4ivn c4inv tap4 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc4iv2p comp4 c4inv pvdd pvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMc4iv2n comp4 c4inv gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\n* =============================================\n* LOGIC (from BVDD)\n* =============================================\nXMinv1p comp1b comp1 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv1n comp1b comp1 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv2p comp2b comp2 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv2n comp2b comp2 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv3p comp3b comp3 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv3n comp3b comp3 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv4p comp4b comp4 bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMinv4n comp4b comp4 gnd  gnd  sky130_fd_pr__nfet_g5v0d10v5 w=20e-6 l=20e-6\n\nXRpo_pu bvdd pass_off gnd sky130_fd_pr__res_xhigh_po w=1 l=50\nXMpo_bufp pass_off comp1b bvdd bvdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_g5v0d10v5 w=40e-6 l=20e-6\nXMpo_b