{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012YMT1kGGmAWNvjC9aDUTYY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The output signals also never cross 1.0V! Looking at the earlier waveform data, the outputs like bypass_en, ea_en etc. were at 0 or tracking BVDD. The issue is that the logic gates are powered from BVDD, and at low BVDD the logic outputs are also low.\n\nAt BVDD=2.5V (comp1 fires): bypass_en should go HIGH. But the logic gates are BVDD-powered. bypass_en_max = BVDD = 2.5V. Crossing 1.0V: yes, if bypass_en goes from 0 to 2.5V, it crosses 1.0V.\n\n\nLet me pull up the saved waveform data to see what bypass_en was actually doing at BVDD=2.5V.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":482,"cache_read_input_tokens":456678,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":482},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"b5b25789-2291-494b-a8e8-e8beed81b538"}
