{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0139XymA7ydtQtDce7RV38FU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Still too high — 230µA. But the expected Iq should be 7V/400kΩ ≈ 17.5µA from the ladder alone. The extra 212µA must be from the PVDD inverter gates drawing current through the logic.\n\nThe issue: when comp outputs are at 5V (PVDD domain) and the BVDD-domain logic gates have BVDD=7V, the logic gate NMOS has Vgs=5V → strongly ON, PFET has Vsg=7-5=2V → also ON. Both ON → crowbar current!\n\nThis is the cross-domain issue: comp outputs at PVDD=5V drive BVDD-domain logic at BVDD=7V. The comp output (5V) is between 0 and BVDD(7V), causing crowbar current in the logic inverters.\n\nThe fix: either level-shift the comp outputs to BVDD domain, or use PVDD-domain logic. For now, let me just cap the comp output to BVDD using a simple clamp.\n\nActually, the simplest fix: just remove the crowbar by making the logic gate PFET see the comp output as \"HIGH enough\" to turn off. With comp=5V and BVDD=7V: PFET Vsg = 7-5 = 2V > |Vthp|=1.01V → ON → crowbar!\n\nTo fix: I need comp to reach BVDD (not just PVDD). Options:\n1. Power the second inverter stage from BVDD instead of PVDD\n2. Add a level shifter between comp and logic\n3. Accept the crowbar and just measure ladder current separately\n\nOption 3 is quickest. The evaluator checks `iq_active_uA` from `run.log`. I can report just the ladder current by measuring it differently. But the spec says \"from BVDD\" which includes ALL current.\n\nLet me try option 1: power the second comp inverter from BVDD. This way comp goes to BVDD, no crowbar."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":180,"cache_read_input_tokens":469262,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":180},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"0f9be3b8-6488-4980-bb0d-ff193868e86a"}
