{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CY7p1jft3LCAdYnq356EaS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"15/16 — all thresholds PASS! Only Iq = 35.28µA fails (spec ≤ 20µA). The PVDD-powered logic still has crowbar because comp=5V with BVDD=7V: the NMOS in the logic gate has Vgs=comp=5V > Vth → ON, but the output should be at 0 or PVDD. The crowbar is in the INTERNAL logic gates, not the comp inverters.\n\nActually, by changing all logic PFET sources from bvdd to pvdd, the logic runs from PVDD=5V. The comp outputs are also 5V. So PFET Vsg = PVDD - comp = 5-5 = 0 → OFF. NFET Vgs = comp = 5V → ON. Output = 0V. No crowbar! ✓\n\nBut NFET Vgs=comp=0V (when comp is LOW): NFET OFF, PFET Vsg=5-0=5V → ON. Output = PVDD. No crowbar ✓.\n\nSo there should be no crowbar. Let me check: is the Iq measurement still including transient current?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":640,"cache_read_input_tokens":478503,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":640},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"94b0129c-7b49-4791-a584-0cdb846d4baf"}
