{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PBNndrAtLc9ZNdY1BHxizq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"35.28µA at BVDD=7V from the BVDD source. The ladder alone should be 7V/400kΩ = 17.5µA. The extra ~18µA comes from... the pass_off pull-up resistor! \n\nXRpo_pu: bvdd to pass_off via 100kΩ resistor (l=50µm → R≈100kΩ). At BVDD=7V with pass_off driven to ~0V by the logic: I = 7V/100kΩ = 70µA! That's huge!\n\nWait, pass_off should be LOW in active mode (comp1=HIGH → comp1b=LOW → pass_off=LOW). The pull-up resistor fights the active driver pulling pass_off LOW. Current = BVDD/R_pullup.\n\nI need to increase the pull-up resistance. With R=500kΩ (l=240µm): I = 7/500k = 14µA. Plus ladder 17.5µA = 31.5µA. Still over.\n\nWith R=2MΩ (l=945µm): I = 3.5µA. Plus 17.5 = 21µA. Close.\n\nWith R=5MΩ (l=2360µm): I = 1.4µA. Plus 17.5 = 18.9µA. Within spec!\n\nBut 2360µm is a very long resistor. Alternatively, just remove the pull-up — it was for POR startup but with PVDD-powered logic, pass_off should default correctly without it."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":463,"cache_read_input_tokens":479143,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":463},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c97cdc95-3b2e-4d91-8a95-126c51f9e013","uuid":"57cf4775-3947-489f-a2d9-0719e551e276"}
